  {
    "type": "NarrativeText",
    "element_id": "f07c6daaadec3284ab0fe0fb902160b4",
    "text": "DSA is the US Govt approved signature scheme, which is designed to provide strong signatures without allowing easy use for encryption. The National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) published Federal Information Processing Standard FIPS 186, known as the Digital Signature Standard (DSS). The DSS makes use of the Secure Hash Algorithm (SHA) described in Chapter 12 and presents a new digital signature technique, the Digital Signature Algorithm (DSA). The DSS was originally proposed in 1991 and revised in 1993 in response to public feedback concerning the security of the scheme. There was a further minor revision in 1996. In 2000, an expanded version of the standard was issued as FIPS 186-2. This latest version also incorporates digital signature algorithms based on RSA and on elliptic curve cryptography. In this section, we discuss the original DSS algorithm. The DSS uses an algorithm that is designed to provide only the digital signature function. Unlike RSA, it cannot be used for encryption or key exchange. Nevertheless, it is a public-key technique.",
    "metadata": {
      "category_depth": 0,
      "file_directory": "data\\raw\\Security",
      "filename": "SCE 422 CH 13 DS - without audio.pptx",
      "last_modified": "2025-01-15T14:22:43",
      "page_number": 6,
      "languages": [
        "eng"
      ],
      "filetype": "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.presentationml.presentation"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "Title",
    "element_id": "7fbc5da9641466e3b61960a03bc9ff1b",
    "text": "Digital Signature Standard (DSS)",
    "metadata": {
      "category_depth": 0,
      "file_directory": "data\\raw\\Security",
      "filename": "SCE 422 CH 13 DS - without audio.pptx",
      "last_modified": "2025-01-15T14:22:43",
      "page_number": 6,
      "languages": [
        "eng"
      ],
      "filetype": "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.presentationml.presentation"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "ListItem",
    "element_id": "22552e82eaef0abbb951cb82c08dd782",
    "text": "US Government approved the DSS signature scheme designed by NIST & NSA in early 90's ",
    "metadata": {
      "category_depth": 0,
      "file_directory": "data\\raw\\Security",
      "filename": "SCE 422 CH 13 DS - without audio.pptx",
      "last_modified": "2025-01-15T14:22:43",
      "page_number": 6,
      "languages": [
        "eng"
      ],
      "filetype": "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.presentationml.presentation",
      "parent_id": "7fbc5da9641466e3b61960a03bc9ff1b"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "ListItem",
    "element_id": "00b6a31a0e0f7cb32610a57c2ce09505",
    "text": "published as FIPS-186 in 1991 and revised in 1993, 1996 & then 2000",
    "metadata": {
      "category_depth": 0,
      "file_directory": "data\\raw\\Security",
      "filename": "SCE 422 CH 13 DS - without audio.pptx",
      "last_modified": "2025-01-15T14:22:43",
      "page_number": 6,
      "languages": [
        "eng"
      ],
      "filetype": "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.presentationml.presentation",
      "parent_id": "7fbc5da9641466e3b61960a03bc9ff1b"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "ListItem",
    "element_id": "8bc6ae7bb24537d58d9db39bccb21562",
    "text": "uses the SHA hash algorithm ",
    "metadata": {
      "category_depth": 0,
      "file_directory": "data\\raw\\Security",
      "filename": "SCE 422 CH 13 DS - without audio.pptx",
      "last_modified": "2025-01-15T14:22:43",
      "page_number": 6,
      "languages": [
        "eng"
      ],
      "filetype": "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.presentationml.presentation",
      "parent_id": "7fbc5da9641466e3b61960a03bc9ff1b"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "ListItem",
    "element_id": "3390fa4fc7efb9fa509daeb348c74ae4",
    "text": "DSS is the standard, DSA is the algorithm",
    "metadata": {
      "category_depth": 0,
      "file_directory": "data\\raw\\Security",
      "filename": "SCE 422 CH 13 DS - without audio.pptx",
      "last_modified": "2025-01-15T14:22:43",
      "page_number": 6,
      "languages": [
        "eng"
      ],
      "filetype": "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.presentationml.presentation",
      "parent_id": "7fbc5da9641466e3b61960a03bc9ff1b"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "ListItem",
    "element_id": "ee9b5e989a0a267cbacb78b9a60638b5",
    "text": "FIPS 186-2 (2000) includes alternative RSA & elliptic curve signature variants",
    "metadata": {
      "category_depth": 0,
      "file_directory": "data\\raw\\Security",
      "filename": "SCE 422 CH 13 DS - without audio.pptx",
      "last_modified": "2025-01-15T14:22:43",
      "page_number": 6,
      "languages": [
        "eng"
      ],
      "filetype": "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.presentationml.presentation",
      "parent_id": "7fbc5da9641466e3b61960a03bc9ff1b"
    }
  },
  {
    "type": "ListItem",
    "element_id": "626f070245663900f074300690cbc2b8",
    "text": "DSA is digital signature only unlike RSA which is a public-key technique",
    "metadata": {
      "category_depth": 0,
      "file_directory": "data\\raw\\Security",
      "filename": "SCE 422 CH 13 DS - without audio.pptx",
